@carlosg : Thanks for the information.

So, the solution is to debug and find why `MetaCompositor` is not initialized for `MetaWorkspace` . Right?
And it can be debugged using GDB. Right?

@lillolollo I switched to multi window mode, and it seems that the main window shows the same wrong behavior as in single window mode.
The toolwindow stays where it should but the window containing the layers is moved to the right when gimp is reopened.
![20190816_1139_29](/uploads/c76844503b4f352fc636c135fa6e9331/20190816_1139_29.webm)

@aklapper 
Sometimes there is a very long chat or something like Freenode-connect or a NickServ with your plain password before the last update of Polari.

I think it would be an excellent addition to add that option for the user. If not, can you tell where the logs files are located?

@Allan - I apologize for my rude comments. I'd edit my message to change it but then you'd look like you were overreacting.

I understand that you are probably working in free time, and I should have understood that my message was not helpful, especially as I myself have given many hours working for free in Open Source projects. I'm sorry.

However, please also do try to understand my frustration when there are major regressions in functionality and usability for no apparent reason from a user point of view, and that life as a long time Linux user is always full of these kinds of things. I'm sorry that you got the brunt of my frustration today.
